# a `std/crypto` extern resolves to the preamble impl in a standalone bundle

Regression for the JS backend (busi deep-offline standalone bundle). Importing a
`std/crypto` extern (`sha256`) emitted `const sha256 = std.crypto.sha256`, where
the namespace member was `(typeof _ssc_ui_sha256 !== 'undefined') ? _ssc_ui_sha256
: undefined` â€” `undefined` under Node, since the host UI stub is absent. That
shadowed the `sha256` â†’ `_sha256` `RuntimeCall` intrinsic (the import also added
`sha256` to `declaredBindings`, disabling the call-site rewrite), so `sha256(...)`
was `not callable`. The extern namespace member now falls back to the intrinsic
target (`_sha256`, guarded by `typeof`) so it resolves to the real preamble impl
under Node while the browser keeps preferring the `_ssc_ui_*` host stub.

[sha256](std/crypto.ssc)

```scalascript
println(sha256("abc"))
```
